# KrishiMitra — Complete Project Walkthrough

## How to Run the Project

You need to start **3 separate services** in **3 separate terminals**, in this order:

---

### 1️⃣ PostgreSQL Database (prerequisite)
Make sure PostgreSQL is running on `localhost:5432` with the database `soil_ml_db` already created.

If the database doesn't exist yet, run this **once**:
```bash
cd c:\Users\Admin\Desktop\Soil\backend
node create_db.js
```
> This connects to the default `postgres` database and creates `soil_ml_db`. The tables are auto-created when the backend starts.

---

### 2️⃣ ML Service (Python FastAPI) — Port 8002
```bash
cd c:\Users\Admin\Desktop\Soil\ml_service
pip install -r requirements.txt          # one-time
uvicorn main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8002 --reload
```
> [!IMPORTANT]
> Start this **before** the backend. The backend calls this service on `http://127.0.0.1:8002`.

---

### 3️⃣ Backend (Node.js Express) — Port 5005
```bash
cd c:\Users\Admin\Desktop\Soil\backend
npm install                              # one-time
npm start
```
> Runs on `http://localhost:5005`. Auto-creates all DB tables on startup via `initDB()`.

---

### 4️⃣ Frontend (React + Vite) — Port 5173
```bash
cd c:\Users\Admin\Desktop\Soil\frontend
npm install                              # one-time
npm run dev
```
> Opens at `http://localhost:5173`. All API requests go to `http://localhost:5005`.

