#### Auth Flow
1. User enters phone number on Login page
2. Frontend calls `POST /api/send-otp` → backend generates OTP (hardcoded `123456` for dev), stores in `otp_store` table, optionally sends via Fast2SMS
3. User enters OTP → Frontend calls `POST /api/verify-otp` → backend verifies against `otp_store`, creates/updates farmer in `farmers` table
4. On success, farmer info is saved to `localStorage('soilai_farmer')`
5. `ProtectedRoute` component checks `localStorage` before allowing access to `/app/*` routes

#### Route Protection
```
/               → Landing (public)
/login          → Login (public)
/app/*          → Protected by ProtectedRoute (checks localStorage)
  /app/analyze       → Analyze
  /app/results       → Results
  /app/insights      → Insights
  /app/history       → History
  /app/communication → SMS Communication
```

