### 🟡 ML Service (Python FastAPI)

**File**: [main.py](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Soil/ml_service/main.py)
**Training Script**: [train_xgboost.py](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Soil/ml_service/train_xgboost.py)
**Dataset**: [Crop_recommendation.csv](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Soil/soil/Crop_recommendation.csv) (in the `soil/` directory)

#### What the ML Model Does
1. **Training** (`train_xgboost.py`):
   - Loads `Crop_recommendation.csv` (22 crops, 7 features: N, P, K, temperature, humidity, pH, rainfall)
   - Encodes crop labels with `LabelEncoder`
   - Scales features with `StandardScaler`
   - Trains an **Ensemble** model: `VotingClassifier(XGBClassifier + RandomForestClassifier)` with soft voting
   - Saves: `crop_xgb_model.pkl`, `scaler.pkl`, `label_encoder.pkl`, `metrics.json`

2. **Inference** (`main.py`):
   - On startup: loads the 3 `.pkl` files + `metrics.json`
   - `POST /api/predict`: Takes soil params → scales → predicts top 2 crops using `predict_proba` → runs rule-based soil health check → returns results
   - `GET /api/metrics`: Returns accuracy, confusion matrix, class list from `metrics.json`

#### Soil Health Check (Rule-Based)
The ML service also runs a **rule-based soil quality assessment**:

| Parameter | Ideal Range | If Low | If High |
|---|---|---|---|
| Nitrogen (N) | 50–150 mg/kg | Add Urea | Use catch crops |
| Phosphorus (P) | 16–45 mg/kg | Add Bone Meal | Avoid P-fertilizers |
| Potassium (K) | ≥120 mg/kg | Add Potash | — |
| pH | 6.0–7.5 | Apply lime | Add compost/sulfur |
| Moisture | 20–80% | Increase irrigation | Improve drainage |

Quality Rating: **Good** (0 issues) → **Moderate** (1-2 issues) → **Poor** (3+ issues)

#### Pre-trained Model Files
| File | Purpose | Size |
|---|---|---|
| `crop_xgb_model.pkl` | Trained XGBoost + RF ensemble | 5.2 MB |
| `scaler.pkl` | StandardScaler fitted on training data | 1.1 KB |
| `label_encoder.pkl` | Maps crop indices ↔ crop names | 830 B |
| `metrics.json` | Accuracy, confusion matrix, class names | 8.8 KB |

