## Summary: How Everything Connects

```
User opens http://localhost:5173
    │
    ├─→ Landing Page (/) → public marketing page
    │
    ├─→ Login (/login)
    │      └─→ POST /api/send-otp  → Backend → PostgreSQL (otp_store) + Fast2SMS
    │      └─→ POST /api/verify-otp → Backend → PostgreSQL (farmers) → localStorage
    │
    └─→ Protected App (/app/*)
           │
           ├── Analyze → POST /predict → Backend → PostgreSQL + ML Service → Results
           ├── Results → Displays data passed via React Router state
           ├── Insights → GET /metrics → Backend → ML Service (metrics.json)
           ├── History → GET /history → Backend → PostgreSQL (JOIN query)
           ├── SMS → POST /api/send-sms → Backend → Fast2SMS
           └── Chatbot (floating) → POST /api/chat → Backend → Google Gemini
```

**The 3 services communicate via HTTP REST APIs. There is no WebSocket or message queue — it's a straightforward request-response architecture.**
